    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.\r\n\r\nI have a C++ class without a nullary constructor, I would like to return an object of such a class by-value from a `cdef` function.\r\n\r\n```cython\r\n# cython: cpp_locals=True, initializedcheck=False\r\n# distutils: language=c++\r\ncdef extern from * nogil:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    struct Foo {\r\n        Foo() = delete;\r\n        int x_;\r\n    };\r\n\r\n    Foo make_foo() {\r\n        return Foo{1};\r\n    }\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n\r\n    cdef cppclass Foo:\r\n        int x_\r\n\r\n    cdef Foo make_foo()\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\ncdef Foo make():\r\n    return make_foo()\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nHowever, AFAICT, even with `cpp_locals`, this does not appear to be possible, since the transpilation of `make` stack-declares an object of type `Foo` without assigning to it:\r\n\r\n```c++\r\n/* \"cython_foo.pyx\":24\r\n * \r\n * \r\n * cdef Foo make():             # <<<<<<<<<<<<<<\r\n *     return make_foo()\r\n */\r\n\r\nstatic Foo __pyx_f_11cython_foo_make(void) {\r\n  Foo __pyx_r;\r\n\r\n  /* \"cython_foo.pyx\":25\r\n * \r\n * cdef Foo make():\r\n *     return make_foo()             # <<<<<<<<<<<<<<\r\n */\r\n  __pyx_r = make_foo();\r\n  goto __pyx_L0;\r\n\r\n  /* \"cython_foo.pyx\":24\r\n * \r\n * \r\n * cdef Foo make():             # <<<<<<<<<<<<<<\r\n *     return make_foo()\r\n */\r\n\r\n  /* function exit code */\r\n  __pyx_L0:;\r\n  return __pyx_r;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like.\r\n\r\nI'd like to be able to do this, and have it work. I'd be happy to have to write some magic assignment statement if necessary.\r\n\r\n### Describe alternatives you've considered.\r\n\r\nI don't think this is possible to work-around since there's no way to inject the \"correct\" C++ code into the definition of `make`.\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": null,
